Depth Learning Layer

What this adds

The system now remembers:
	•	what kind of problem it saw
	•	what depth it chose
	•	how many passes it used
	•	whether the result was grounded
	•	whether the external check passed
	•	whether the artifact was useful
	•	what the real-world outcome was

Then it uses that history to bias future depth decisions.

So it moves from:

rule-based adaptive depth

to:

experience-shaped adaptive depth

