What changed structurally

v1
	•	chooses depth from current conditions

v2
	•	chooses depth from current conditions
	•	then nudges depth using historical outcomes
	•	stores results for future learning

So now the system can start discovering things like:
	•	“High novelty + weak evidence usually needs depth 4”
	•	“Moderate uncertainty but strong evidence only needs depth 2”
	•	“Depth 5 produces worse outcomes for this class of problem”

⸻

Pantheon mapping
	•	Hound: scores uncertainty, impact, conflict, evidence quality
	•	Conductor: picks baseline depth
	•	EchoFrame: stores depth decisions and outcomes
	•	Mirror: checks whether recursion improved or degraded the result
	•	Adaptive Depth Learner: remembers which depths actually paid off
	•	Hephaestus: forces artifact output
	•	Mother Duck: persistent ledger of reasoning-depth performance

