Canonical doctrine addition

Use this in the repo:

Adaptive Depth Learning Invariant:
Reasoning depth should not only respond to present uncertainty, but also to remembered performance.
The system must learn which depths produce the highest real-world value for each class of problem.
Confidence alone does not justify depth.
Outcomes, grounded artifacts, and external feedback are the final judges.


